
[1]egregious

   EGRE'GIOUS, a. [L. egregius, supposed to be from e or ex grege, from or
   out of or beyond the herd, select, choice.]

   1. Eminent; remarkable; extraordinary; distinguished; as egregious
   exploits; an egregious prince. But in this sense it is seldom applied
   to persons.

   2. In a bad sense, great; extraordinary; remarkable; enormous; as an
   egregious mistake; egregious contempt. In this sense it is often
   applied to persons; as an egregious rascal; an egregious murderer.
